{"body": "If the remote_function is used to generate code in a script tag then it will fail however leaving it as is means it works in both contexts (but may not validate properly). The proper fix should be to remove the html_safe call and let the whole javascript string be entity escaped. That way you can use the raw helper when you need to use it within a javascript context.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/403492", "created_at": "2010-09-13T09:21:29Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5#issuecomment-403492", "updated_at": "2010-09-13T09:21:29Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/pixeltrix", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/b14001f2b40640dd6cb63f0e8f1f4869?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7cb36e23529e4de4c41460940cc85e6e.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/received_events", "gravatar_id": "b14001f2b40640dd6cb63f0e8f1f4869", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "pixeltrix", "type": "User", "id": 6321, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pixeltrix/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386edfbd3543c151012e7f"}, "id": 403492, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5"}
